divs: sighting details10 to 11 i went out to walk the dog, looked up as i usually do, and saw what appeared to be a plane. i live on a flight pattern for our international, and municipal airports. however it was well over the normal cruising altitude of commercial aircraft, and the size, and intensity of the spec of light seemed much larger at that height. an estimate would be 60-80000ft. only white light visible, that what you would see looking at a star. no strobes or colors. and no sound. i observed this guy move from north to the south east what i can only guess, real fast. in the amount of sky that we see, this object covered about 2\3rds of that in 20-30 seconds, north to south, turned to the south east, and then accelerated so fast it seemed to make the light source fade out. about 2-3 seconds. or he shut the light off very slowly? the sky is super clear tonight, and i can normally i.d. a plane. i,m now confused... anyone?
Summary: very high altitude control flight from north to south east.
